name: hdc_integration_test
version: "1.0.0"
language: zig
module: hdc_integration_test

description: |
  HDC Integration Test — Level 10A.12: Full Pipeline Validation Suite.
  Tests the complete chain: train → save → load → verify → stream → swarm.
  Each test is a concrete, falsifiable claim about system behavior.

  === THE GAP THIS CLOSES ===
  24 Level 10A specs define the architecture. 0 integration tests validate the
  full pipeline end-to-end. This spec creates concrete integration tests that
  exercise the real pipeline across spec boundaries.

  === TEST SUITE ===

  TEST 1: MODEL PERSISTENCE FIDELITY
    Train model on Shakespeare (10 epochs) → save as .trinity file → load back.
    Fidelity check: for all roles, cosineSimilarity(saved, loaded) == 1.0 exactly.
    File size check: .trinity file is ~4,504 bytes (header 32 + codebook 3850 +
      roles 594 + meta 28 + CRC 4).
    CRC check: CRC32 of content matches stored CRC32.
    Round-trip: save → load → forward → decode → same predictions as before save.

    .trinity format (from v2.23 model_persistence spec):
      Bytes 0-3:    Magic "TRN\x01"
      Bytes 4-5:    Version (1, 0)
      Bytes 6-7:    Dimension (256)
      Bytes 8-9:    Vocab size (~70)
      Bytes 10-11:  Num roles (11)
      Bytes 12-15:  Num heads (3)
      Bytes 16-19:  Context size (8)
      Bytes 20-23:  Codebook offset
      Bytes 24-27:  Roles offset
      Bytes 28-31:  Metadata offset
      Bytes 32-3881: Codebook (70 chars * 52 bytes packed + 5 bytes header each)
      Bytes 3882-4475: Roles (11 * 52 bytes packed + 2 bytes header each)
      Bytes 4476-4503: Metadata (epochs, loss, timestamp)
      Bytes 4500-4503: CRC32 checksum

    Packed format: 5 trits per byte → 256 trits = 52 bytes per vector.
    70 codebook entries: 70 * (52 + 5) = 3,990 bytes (approximate)
    11 role vectors: 11 * (52 + 2) = 594 bytes

  TEST 2: STREAMING 200+ TOKENS
    Train model (10 epochs) → generate 200 tokens with greedy decoding.
    Measure:
      - Total generation time (expected: 200 * ~170 us = ~34 ms)
      - Tokens per second (expected: ~5,800)
      - Unique ratio: count(unique chars) / 200 (target: > 0.10 = 10%+)
      - Repetition rate: consecutive duplicates / 200 (target: < 0.15 = 15%)
      - Valid characters: all outputs are in vocabulary (target: 100%)

    Generation protocol:
      1. Seed: first 8 chars from corpus
      2. For i in 0..200:
         a. context = last 8 generated tokens
         b. output_hv = forward(context)  // with KV-cache if available
         c. next_char = codebook.decode(output_hv)  // greedy: argmax similarity
         d. confidence = max(similarities)
         e. append next_char to output
         f. record latency
      3. Report quality metrics

  TEST 3: SWARM SIMULATION (10 NODES)
    Simulate 10-node federated learning with BFT majority-vote bundling.

    Protocol:
      1. Partition corpus into 10 shards (each node gets ~100 chars)
      2. Each node trains independently for 5 epochs (local roles only)
      3. Sync round: collect all 10 role sets
      4. For each role r:
         global_role[r] = sequential_bundle(node0_role[r], ..., node9_role[r])
         Implementation: acc = roles[0]
                        for i in 1..10: acc = vsa.bundle2(acc, roles[i])
      5. Distribute global_role back to all nodes
      6. Each node evaluates on shared eval set
      7. Verify: post-sync eval_loss < pre-sync eval_loss (sync improved quality)

    Communication cost:
      Per round: 10 nodes * 11 roles * 52 bytes = 5,720 bytes
      Expected: 5.7 KB per sync round

    Byzantine test:
      8. Inject 2 Byzantine nodes (random role vectors instead of trained)
      9. Repeat sync with 10 nodes (8 honest + 2 Byzantine)
      10. Verify: global roles still similar to honest-only aggregate
          cosineSimilarity(global_with_byz, global_honest) > 0.6
          (majority vote should reject < 50% Byzantine)

  TEST 4: PREDICTION ACCURACY IMPROVEMENT
    Before training: forward 100 samples, record accuracy (expect ~1.4% = 1/70).
    After training (10 epochs): forward same 100 samples, record accuracy.
    Verify: post_accuracy > pre_accuracy (training actually improved predictions).
    Target: post_accuracy > 10% (at least 7x improvement over random baseline).

  TEST 5: ROLE ORTHOGONALITY
    After training, verify role vectors remain approximately orthogonal.
    For all pairs (role_i, role_j) where i != j:
      cosineSimilarity(role_i, role_j) should be < 0.3
    If any pair > 0.6: role collapse detected (spec failure).
    Expected: D=256 gives random orthogonality ~0.06, training shouldn't
    push roles far from orthogonal.

  === PASS/FAIL CRITERIA ===
  All 5 tests must pass for "Level 10A Integration: VERIFIED".
  Any failure identifies a specific gap between spec and reality.

  Trinity Identity: phi^2 + 1/phi^2 = 3
  Sacred Formula: V = n * 3^k * pi^m * phi^p * e^q

types:
  PersistenceTest:
    fields:
      file_size_bytes: usize
      expected_size_bytes: usize
      size_match: Bool
      crc_valid: Bool
      role_fidelity: List<Float>
      all_roles_exact: Bool
      round_trip_predictions_match: Bool
      passed: Bool

  StreamingTest:
    fields:
      tokens_generated: usize
      total_time_ms: Float
      tokens_per_second: Float
      unique_ratio: Float
      repetition_rate: Float
      all_valid_chars: Bool
      avg_confidence: Float
      min_confidence: Float
      generated_text: String
      passed: Bool

  SwarmSyncResult:
    fields:
      num_nodes: usize
      pre_sync_eval_losses: List<Float>
      post_sync_eval_loss: Float
      sync_improved: Bool
      communication_bytes: usize
      sync_time_ms: Float

  ByzantineTest:
    fields:
      honest_nodes: usize
      byzantine_nodes: usize
      global_honest_similarity: Float
      global_byz_similarity: Float
      bft_tolerance_held: Bool
      passed: Bool

  SwarmTest:
    fields:
      sync_result: SwarmSyncResult
      byzantine_result: ByzantineTest
      passed: Bool

  AccuracyTest:
    fields:
      pre_training_accuracy: Float
      post_training_accuracy: Float
      improvement_factor: Float
      target_met: Bool
      passed: Bool

  OrthogonalityTest:
    fields:
      role_pairs_checked: usize
      max_similarity: Float
      avg_similarity: Float
      collapse_detected: Bool
      passed: Bool

  IntegrationReport:
    fields:
      persistence: PersistenceTest
      streaming: StreamingTest
      swarm: SwarmTest
      accuracy: AccuracyTest
      orthogonality: OrthogonalityTest
      all_passed: Bool
      timestamp: String

behaviors:
  - name: initIntegrationSuite
    given: D=256, H=3, inline Shakespeare corpus
    when: Build codebook, init roles, prepare corpus, set up test harness
    then: Integration test suite ready

  - name: trainBaselineModel
    given: Training corpus (812 samples) and 10-epoch schedule
    when: Train with no-backprop (bind+sparsify+bundle2), LR schedule phase 1-3
    then: Trained model ready for integration tests

  - name: testPersistence
    given: Trained model (codebook + 11 roles)
    when: |
      1. Save to .trinity file (packed trits, 5 per byte)
      2. Verify file size matches expected (~4,504 bytes)
      3. Load from .trinity file
      4. Compare each role: cosineSimilarity(saved, loaded)
      5. Verify CRC32 integrity
      6. Forward 10 samples with loaded model, compare predictions to pre-save
    then: PersistenceTest with fidelity metrics

  - name: testStreaming200
    given: Trained model and 8-char seed text
    when: |
      Generate 200 tokens via greedy decoding:
      For each step: forward(last 8 tokens) → decode(argmax) → append
      Record per-token latency, confidence, character
    then: StreamingTest with quality metrics and generated text

  - name: testSwarmSync
    given: Corpus partitioned into 10 shards
    when: |
      1. 10 independent training runs (5 epochs each on local shard)
      2. Collect all role sets
      3. Majority-vote bundle: global = sequential_bundle2(all node roles)
      4. Distribute global roles
      5. Evaluate pre-sync and post-sync on shared eval set
    then: SwarmSyncResult proving sync improves quality

  - name: testByzantineTolerance
    given: 8 honestly-trained nodes + 2 Byzantine nodes (random roles)
    when: |
      1. Bundle all 10 (including Byzantine) via sequential bundle2
      2. Bundle honest-only 8 via sequential bundle2
      3. Compare: cosineSimilarity(global_all, global_honest)
    then: ByzantineTest proving majority vote rejects < 50% adversaries

  - name: testAccuracyImprovement
    given: 100 test samples, model before and after training
    when: |
      Pre-training: forward 100 samples, count correct predictions
      Post-training: forward same 100 samples, count correct predictions
    then: AccuracyTest proving training increases accuracy above baseline

  - name: testRoleOrthogonality
    given: 11 trained role vectors
    when: |
      For all pairs (i, j) where i < j:
        sim = cosineSimilarity(role[i], role[j])
        if sim > 0.6: flag collapse
    then: OrthogonalityTest with max/avg pairwise similarity

  - name: runFullIntegrationSuite
    given: All test functions and trained model
    when: Execute testPersistence, testStreaming200, testSwarmSync, testByzantineTolerance, testAccuracyImprovement, testRoleOrthogonality
    then: IntegrationReport with per-test pass/fail and overall verdict

  - name: generateIntegrationReport
    given: IntegrationReport
    when: Format as markdown with per-test details, metrics, pass/fail summary
    then: Complete integration test report for documentation

test_cases:
  - name: persistence_round_trip
    description: Save and load .trinity file preserves exact role vectors
    expected: all_roles_exact = true, crc_valid = true

  - name: streaming_200_tokens
    description: Generate 200 tokens with reasonable quality
    expected: tokens_generated >= 200, unique_ratio > 0.10, all_valid_chars = true

  - name: streaming_throughput
    description: Generation throughput exceeds 1000 tokens/sec
    expected: tokens_per_second > 1000

  - name: swarm_sync_improves
    description: Federated sync improves eval loss vs individual training
    expected: sync_improved = true

  - name: bft_rejects_byzantine
    description: 2/10 Byzantine nodes do not corrupt global model
    expected: bft_tolerance_held = true

  - name: training_improves_accuracy
    description: Post-training accuracy exceeds pre-training by 7x+
    expected: improvement_factor > 7.0

  - name: no_role_collapse
    description: All role pairs have cosine similarity < 0.6
    expected: collapse_detected = false
